      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PEWTER PEARL (1) gets the blinkers on first time today with the 3kg claim of Bent coming in handy. She didn't jump well last start at the Sapphire Coast and was beaten 2L there following a good win at Moruya two back. Can bounce back to winning ways in what looks a very suitable assignment. BAYCAT (2) will be fitter for a couple of Warwick Farm trials and was a first-up winner last campaign at Canberra. Should be prominent from the outset under Brookes and and will be tough to run down. CALLENEM THRU (3) just missed at Canberra before the break and has since joined the Rob Potter barn. She boasts a good record at this trip and did jump favourite before the break, with that form working out well. She creates plenty of interest. MINKS WRITTEN (10) is better than what she showed last start and can return to form. SALMA'S STAR (5) is third-up now and is a track and trip winner previously. Can bounce back to her best.",
